	$779.8 million


	 of


	loss


	, net of tax, in


	2014


	.




	The fluctuation in Discontinued operations in


	2015


	 compared to


	2014


	 was mainly related to a decrease in income tax benefit of


	$282.7 million


	, an increase in impairment charges of 


	$230.7 million


	 and a decrease in income from operations due to the sale of the Men’s Health and Prostate Health components. The decrease in income tax expense benefit relates to the tax impact of the underlying differences between book and tax basis of the underlying assets sold as part of the transactions in 2014 and 2015. These fluctuations were partially offset by a decrease in expense associated with mesh-related product liability claimants of


	$165.6 million


	 and a gain on the sale of the Men’s Health and Prostate Health components of approximately


	$13.6 million


	 in


	2015


	.




