	. In June 2016, the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office issued Endo a new Vasostrict



	®



	 patent, which has an expiration date of January 30, 2035. Any Abbreviated New Drug Application (ANDA) applicant seeking FDA approval for a generic version of Vasostrict



	®



	prior to expiration of the patent has to notify Par of its ANDA filing before it can obtain FDA approval. Any ANDA filer whose application was not received prior to submission of the new patent information would be subject to a 30-month stay of marketing approval by the FDA upon the initiation of Hatch-Waxman litigation by Par against the ANDA filer.




