	Paladin Labs Inc. Acquisition




	On


	February 28, 2014


	 (the Paladin Acquisition Date), the Company acquired all of the shares of Paladin Labs Inc. (Paladin) Under the terms of the transaction, former Paladin shareholders received


	1.6331


	 Endo ordinary shares, or


	35.5 million


	 shares, and


	C$1.16


	 in cash, for total consideration of


	$2.87 billion


	 as of February 28, 2014.




	Paladin is a specialty pharmaceutical company headquartered in Montreal, Canada, focused on acquiring and in-licensing innovative pharmaceutical products for the Canadian and world markets. Paladin’s key products serve growing therapeutic areas, including attention deficit hyperactivity disorder (ADHD), pain, and urology. In addition to its Canadian operations, as of the Paladin Acquisition Date, Paladin owned a controlling interest in Laboratorios Paladin de Mexico S.A. in Mexico and in publicly traded Litha in South Africa.




	The operating results of Paladin are included in the accompanying


	Consolidated Statements of Operations


	 for the


	years


	 ended


	December 31, 2016


	 and


	2015


	 and the operating results from the acquisition date of


	February 28, 2014


	 are included in the accompanying


	Consolidated Statements of Operations


	 for the


	year


	 ended


	December 31, 2014


	. The


	Consolidated Balance Sheets


	 as of


	December 31, 2016


	 and


	2015


	 reflect the acquisition of Paladin. Our measurement period adjustments for Paladin were complete as of


	February 28, 2015


	.




