	Effective December 19, 2012, the Company and Grünenthal amended the Grünenthal Agreement whereby the Company became responsible for planning of packaging of finished product and certain other routine packaging quality obligations and Grünenthal agreed to reimburse the Company for the third-party costs incurred related to packaging as well as pay the Company a periodic packaging fee. The amendment also changed certain of the terms with respect to the floor price required to be paid by the Company in consideration for product supplied by Grünenthal. On February 18, 2014, the Company and Grünenthal amended the Grünenthal Agreement to define the responsibilities of the parties for certain additional clinical work to be performed for OPANA



