	NOTE 16. SHAREHOLDERS' EQUITY




	On February 11, 2014, the Company issued


	4,000,000


	 euro deferred shares of US


	$0.01


	 each at par. The euro deferred shares are held by nominees in order to satisfy an Irish legislative requirement to maintain a minimum level of issued share capital denominated in euro and to have at least seven registered shareholders. The euro deferred shares carry no voting rights and are not entitled to receive any dividend or distribution.








